latestPosts.caption:
Wanting certain answers led me to saying a yes to visit the kumbh. Obviously never was it in my must visit places, but this year I literally got sold to the marketing of Kumbh done! The questions that I was so inquisite about was; 
What is this Sangam point ? the point where the brown water of the Ganga meets the green water of the Yamuna, along with the mythical Saraswati, which remains unseen but believed to run underground.

Why was Maha Kumbh so special this year? Maha kumbh happens every 12 years and Kumbh happens every 4 years but what made it special this year was due to its alignment with rare celestial configurations(all planets coming in one line) that occur once every 144 years. Incidentally Maha Kumbh happened this year & thus the dip was essential to calm the planetary effects. 

The experience:
•The city is a mess with unexpected overflow of crowd that the restaurants and hotels are not able to serve to. The order takes a minimum of 45 mins! 

•Beware about the hotel bookings, as they show something else and if they get a walk in who’s ready to pay a higher amount they will cancel your booking saying ‘no electricity’ and shift you to a 1 star or less which looks like a lodge! However the hotels are running full capacity there! 

•Wish people were self aware about cleanliness & hygiene. Saw piles of clothes lying because ppl left the dip clothes everywhere! 
Lastly, I didn’t lose anyone in Kumbh Ka Mela 🤣
.
.
.
.
.
